This unpretentious font is complemented by the regular, yet organic silhouette of a Bavarian pretzel. Brezel Grotesk, originally designed by Stefanie Preis in 2010, was later refined and further developed by Milieu Grotesque and Bj\u00F6 rn Gogalla until 2014. The family comes in eight styles in total (four weights with corresponding italics), each style comprises an extended Latin character set.
